Required Items Checklist To setup your Raspberry Pi, you will typically need the following items:
SD Card loaded with a supported operating system
HDMI monitor or a display that has RCA composite video input (HDMI monitor highly recommended)
HDMI cable or RCA cable if using an analog composite display
Standard USB Keyboard and Mouse
Micro USB Power Supply (adapter) capable of delivering 1A @ 5.0V
[Optional] Ethernet cable for connection to a wired network
[Optional] USB WiFi Dongle/Adapter supported by the operating system
[Optional] A case to hold and protect your Raspberry Pi
